Subject: Re: [T2] air intake boot

I haven't tried it yet, but have thought of cleaning my "S" boot very well 
and then either dipping it or painting it with the tool "dip" product
sold at Lowe's and other hardware stores.

You know, the stuff you use to dip tool handles in that gives them
a "plastic" soft grip.

It can be bought in various colors and the instructions say that you can 
actually paint it if you thin it a little.

It is still flexible and should look nice as well.  If have used the stuff 
on some tool handles and it's still there many years later.

Just a thought....I buy a lot of car parts at the Hardware store<grin>.

Cheers, dave

